# Mentor (Socrates)

`MentorBubble.tsx` is the AI chat component. It calls an OpenAI-compatible **`POST …/chat/completions`** endpoint via `fetch` from the browser. Base URL, model, and optional API key come from `NessoSettings` (`aiBaseUrl`, `aiModel`, `aiApiKey`); there is no environment-variable fallback for the key.

## Setup

Configure the mentor under **Settings** (gear, **⌘,**). Defaults target **Ollama** at `http://localhost:11434/v1` with a local model name (e.g. `gemma2:2b`); no bearer token is required for typical local setups. Keys are client-side by design — do not deploy publicly with secrets embedded.

## Persona

Socrates is a Socratic mentor: he asks short, pointed questions rather than explaining. Shared rules live in `MENTOR_BASE` inside `MentorBubble.tsx`:

- Never generate graph content (no proposing new nodes or edges).
- Prefer one short question over a long explanation; keep replies under ~90 words.
- No emojis, no flattery.
- Markdown emphasis with `*asterisks*` for key words.

## Modes and system prompt

Three tabs set `mode`: **`gap`** (Review), **`explore`** (Exploration), **`bootstrap`** (Bootstrap). `buildSystemPrompt()` returns the full system string for the active mode.

- **Review** — `priorityNodes()` queues concepts with `conf < 4` or `daysAgo(reviewedAt) > 14`, sorted by weakness. `buildReviewPrompt(node)` focuses the model on one concept. Users rate with in-panel controls; `updateNodeData` sets `reviewedAt: Date.now()` and the assistant continues with the next queued node until the session completes.
- **Exploration** — Lists nodes (and up to 20 edges) plus optional selection context (selected node or edge type). Free Q&A about the graph; still must not invent nodes/edges for the user.
- **Bootstrap** — Optional `.txt`/`.md` file loads text into local state (`bootstrapText`, first ~3000 chars in prompt). Helps reason about concepts to map; still no automated graph edits.

On panel open / graph switch / `sessionKey` bump / bootstrap text load, the first mentor line is fetched by **POST**ing a synthetic user seed (“Start the review session…”, “Hello, I want to explore…”, etc.) with the appropriate system prompt — not a static `SOCRATIC_PROMPTS` opening.

## Selection vs history

`history` remains local component state. Mode or graph changes reset the session (`sessionKey`, queue index). Exploration mode uses `selectedNode` / `selectedEdge` only as optional context inside `buildSystemPrompt`, not as a trigger for static per-selection openers from `seedGraph.ts`.

## Panel open/closed

Whether the mentor **card** is expanded is `mentorPanelExpanded` on `useGraphStore`, updated via `setMentorPanelExpanded`. It is persisted with the rest of UI chrome (`zustand` `persist` → localStorage). The FAB remains visible when collapsed.

## Message history

`history: Message[]` is local to `MentorBubble` (not in the store). It resets when the mentor session restarts (panel open, mode tab, graph id, bootstrap load, `sessionKey`). Do not persist chat history to the store.

## API call

`fetch(`${aiBaseUrl}/chat/completions`, …)` with JSON body:

- `model` — `settings.aiModel`
- `max_tokens` — `300`
- `messages` — `[{ role: 'system', content: buildSystemPrompt() }, …]` plus full `history` turns mapped to `user` / `assistant` roles (initial mentor reply comes from the same assistant role in the thread).

`Authorization: Bearer …` is sent when `settings.aiApiKey` is non-empty.
